Key.English: You have to free the island from all enemy forces.
Key.Spanish: Tiene que liberar la isla de todas las fuerzas enemigas.
Key.Portuguese: Tem que libertar a ilha de todas as forças inimigas.
Key.Korean: 귀관은 적군의 손아귀에서 부터 이 섬을 해방시켜야합니다.
Key.Japanese: すべての敵軍から島を解放しなければなりません。
Key.Original: You have to free the island from all enemy forces.
Key.Russian: Вам необходимо освободить территорию острова от врагов.
Key.Chinesesimp: 你需要从敌人手里解放这个岛屿.

Key.English: To clear a target kill all enemies, destroy the radio tower at the main target site, solve the main target sidemission and capture all depots.
Key.Spanish: Para conquistar el objetivo hay que matar a todos los enemigos, destruir la torre de radio de la misión principal, resolver la misión adicional y capturar todos los campamentos.
Key.Portuguese: Para aclarar um objetivo mata todos os inimigos, destruir a torre radiofónica no lugar de objetivo principal, solucionar o objetivo principal sidemission e capturar todos os depósitos.
Key.Korean: 목적를 달성하기 위해서는 작전지역에 존재하는 모두 적 병력을 소탕, 통신탑을 파괴한 뒤, 주요 미션과 보조 과제를 완수하시면 됩니다.
Key.Japanese: ターゲットをクリアするには、すべての敵を殺し、メインターゲットサイトのラジオタワーを破壊し、メインターゲットとサイドミッションを解決し、すべてのデポをキャプチャします。
Key.Original: To clear a target kill all enemies, destroy the radio tower at the main target site, solve the main target sidemission and capture all depots.
Key.Russian: Чтобы выполнить Главное Задание (города), Вам нужно убить всех ИИ противников, взорвать радиовышку, захватить все блокпосты и выполнить второстепенную городскую задачу.
Key.Chinesesimp: 你的任务是消灭全部敌人,摧毁目标区域的主通讯塔,完成支线任务并占领所有的军需库.

Key.English: There are several side missions available that will get you some extra vehicles if you solve them.
Key.Spanish: Hay varias misiones secundarias disponibles, que si las resuelve, podrá conseguir algunos vehículos adicionales.
Key.Portuguese: Há várias missões de lado disponíveis que conseguirá você alguns veículos extras se lhes soluciona.
Key.Korean: 보조 과제을 완수할 경우, 추가적인 보상 또한 받으실 수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: 解決するとボーナス車両が得られるサイドミッションがあります
Key.Original: There are several side missions available that will get you some extra vehicles if you solve them.
Key.Russian: Так же существуют отдельные ДОП.ЗАДАНИЯ, за выполнение которых Вы получаете боевую ПРИЗОВУЮ технику.
Key.Chinesesimp: 如果你完成了支线任务将会获得额外的载具奖励

Key.English: Once a main target is clear, a flag gets created in a random place from where you can jump with the HALO parajump script (if enabled, not available in the TT version).
Key.Spanish: Una vez que la misión principal esté conquistada, se creará una bandera al azar en el lugar, desde donde se puede saltar en paracaídas (si está activado, no disponible en la versión TT).
Key.Portuguese: Uma vez um objetivo principal é claro, uma bandeira consegue criada em um lugar aleatório de onde pode você saltar com o HALO parajump guião (se habilitado, não disponível no TT versão).
Key.Korean: 주목적지를 탈환하게되면, 깃대가 무작위 위치로 생성되며 해당 위치에서 공수 낙하 기능을 사용하실 수 있습니다. (활성화했을경우. TvT전에서는 사용하실 수 없습니다.
Key.Japanese: メインターゲットがクリアされると、HALOparajumpスクリプトでパラジャンプできる旗が作成されます（サーバー設定で有効な場合。TTバージョンでは使用できません）。
Key.Original: Once a main target is clear, a flag gets created in a random place from where you can jump with the HALO parajump script (if enabled, not available in the TT version).
Key.Russian: Когда город захвачен, в нем создается флаг для десантирования (эвакуации игрока). Так же он есть на базах сторон.
Key.Chinesesimp: 当一个主要的目标被清理完毕，将会出现一个随机的旗子并在旗子处生成一个HALO跳伞点 (如果启用, 在TT版本中不可用).

Key.English: You can transport all vehicles with your lift choppers.
Key.Spanish: Puede transportar todos los vehículos con sus helicópteros de transporte.
Key.Portuguese: Pode transportar todos os veículos com vosso elevador choppers.
Key.Korean: 차량 수송용 헬리콥터를 이용하여 모든 차량을 수송하실 수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: 空輸ヘリコプターですべての車両を輸送することができます。
Key.Original: You can transport all vehicles with your lift choppers.
Key.Russian: Вы можете перевозить технику специальным транспортным вертолетом.
Key.Chinesesimp: 你可以用你的吊运直升机吊运所有的载具.

Key.English: The MHQs are your mobile respawn points.
Key.Spanish: Los MHQs son sus puntos de reapariciones móviles.
Key.Portuguese: O MHQs é vosso móvel respawn pontos
Key.Japanese: MHQは、あなたの移動復活ポイントです。
Key.Original: The MHQs are your mobile respawn points.
Key.Russian: КШМ это Ваша мобильная точка возрождения. КШМ всего две.
Key.Chinesesimp: 基地车是可以移动的重生点.

Key.English: You can drop an ammo crate from a MHQ or if you are the pilot of a helicopter (but you have to load a crate at base first)!
Key.Spanish: Puede cargar una caja de munición en un MHQ o si es piloto de un helicóptero (pero hay que cargar primero una caja en la base)
Key.Portuguese: Pode carregar uma caixa de munição em um MHQ ou se é piloto de um helicóptero (mas Heno que carregar primeiro uma caixa na base)
Key.Korean: 탄약상자 적재소(Ammo Point)에서 지휘차량에 탄약상자를 적재할 수 있습니다. 귀관이 헬리콥터 파일럿인 경우 헬리콥터에서도 같은 기능을 이용 하실 수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: あなたはMHQから弾薬箱を降ろすことができます。もしあなたがヘリコプターの操縦士であればヘリコプターからも（しかし、最初にベースで積み込む必要があります）！
Key.Original: You can drop an ammo crate from a MHQ or if you are the pilot of a helicopter (but you have to load a crate at base first)!
Key.Russian: Вы можете перевозить ящик-арсенал в КШМ или в специальных вертолетах, предварительно загрузив его на базе.
Key.Chinesesimp: 你可以从基地车中放下弹药箱,如果你是直升机驾驶员也可以从直升机上放下弹药箱(前提是你要先到弹药箱提取点装载弹药箱)!

Key.English: The maximum number of ammo crates simultaneously is %1. An ammo crate gets only deleted if the crate was destroyed.
Key.Spanish: El número máximo de cajas de munición de forma simultánea es %1. La caja de munición sólo se elimina si es destruída.
Key.Portuguese: O número máximo de ammo crates simultaneamente é %1. Um ammo crate consegue só eliminado se o crate esteve destruído.
Key.Korean: 탄약상자의 최대 소환 한도는 %1 입니다. 탄약상자는 오직 파괴될 경우에만 제거됩니다.
Key.Japanese: 同時に置ける弾薬箱の最大数は%1です。 弾薬箱が破壊された場合にのみ、弾薬箱が削除されます。
Key.Original: The maximum number of ammo crates simultaneously is %1. An ammo crate gets only deleted if the crate was destroyed.
Key.Russian: Максимальное одновременное количество ящиков-арсеналов на карте %1. Чтобы выгружать новые Вам необходимо удалить предыдущие.
Key.Chinesesimp: 弹药箱的上限是 %1. 弹药箱只有被摧毁才会消失.

Key.English: Reload a crate into chopper 1,2,3 or W or in one of the MHQs, otherwise you will end up at the next target without any crate.
Key.Spanish: Cargue una caja en el helicóptero 1,2,3 o W y en uno de los MHQs, de lo contrario el resultado final será en el próximo objetivo sin munición.
Key.Portuguese: Reload Um crate a chopper 1,2,3 ou W ou em um do MHQs, otherwise acabará no objetivo próximo sem qualquer crate.
Key.Korean: 탄약상자를 사용하시고 꼭 다시 실어주십시오. 탄약상자는 자동으로 생성되거나 제거되지 않습니다.
Key.Japanese: 弾薬箱をヘリコプター1,2,3またはWまたはMHQのいずれかに再装填します。そうしないと、弾薬箱なしで次のターゲットに行くことになります。
Key.Original: Reload a crate into chopper 1,2,3 or W or in one of the MHQs, otherwise you will end up at the next target without any crate.
Key.Russian: Не забывайте загружать ящик после выполненного задания обратно в транспорт, чтобы на новой миссии не остаться без арсенала.
Key.Chinesesimp: 重新将弹药箱放进直升机或基地车内,否则下一个任务你可能没有弹药箱补给.

Key.English: Once deployed you can teleport from one MHQ to the other, enable satellite view or create a bike.
Key.Spanish: Una vez desplegado el MHQ se puede teletransportar de uno a otro, permite la vista de satélite o sacar una moto.
Key.Portuguese: Reload Um crate a chopper 1,2,3 ou W ou em um do MHQs, otherwise acabará no objetivo próximo sem qualquer crate.
Key.Korean: 지휘차량을 전개(Deploy)하면 순간이동(Teleport) 기능이 활성화 됩니다. 위성관측(Satellite view)를 통한 정찰기능또한 사용하실수있으시며, Quadbike 및 고기동경량차량인 Prowler를 소환 하실 수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: 一度展開すると、あるMHQから別のMHQにテレポートしたり、衛星視点を有効にしたり、乗り物を出すことができます。
Key.Original: Once deployed you can teleport from one MHQ to the other, enable satellite view or create a bike.
Key.Russian: Так же в КШМ Вам доступен квадроцикл, спутниковое наблюдение и вызов БПЛА (стационарно).
Key.Chinesesimp: 展开基地车后,你可以传送到基地车旁,并可以使用卫星监控,也可以通过基地车取得摩托车.

Key.English: The engineers can repair and refuel all vehicles and aircraft (needs ToolKit and only available in engineer full mode).
Key.Spanish: Los ingenieros pueden reparar y repostar todos los vehículos y aeronaves (Es necesario un kit de herramientas y sólo está disponible en modo de ingeniero).
Key.Portuguese: Os engenheiros podem consertar e refuel todos os veículos e aeronave (necessidades ToolKit e únicos disponíveis em engenheiro modo cheio).
Key.Korean: 공병은 모든 차량과 항공기를 수리 혹은 보급할 수 있습니다. 도구모음을 가지고 있어야합니다.
Key.Japanese: エンジニアは、すべての車両と航空機を修理して補給することができます（ツールキットが必要、エンジニアフルモードでのみ使用可能）。
Key.Original: The engineers can repair and refuel all vehicles and aircraft (needs ToolKit and only available in engineer full mode).
Key.Russian: Инженеры как всегда могут ремонтировать всю технику и при определенных настройках миссии им требуется ремнабор.
Key.Chinesesimp: 工程兵可以修理并给载具和飞行器加油(需要工具包ToolKit，仅在工程兵模式有效).

Key.English: That only works once if no engineer truck or repair truck is near an engineer (reload and refuel capability can be restored at base).
Key.Spanish: Sólo funciona una vez, si no hay camión de ingeniero o de reparaciones y debe está cerca un ingeniero (recargar y repostar se puede hacer también en la base).
Key.Portuguese: Aqueles trabalhos únicos uma vez se nenhum caminhão de engenheiro ou caminhão de reparo é perto um engenheiro (reload e refuel a capacidade pode ser restaurada em base).
Key.Korean: 공병 트럭 혹은 수리 트럭은 공병이 주위에 없을 경우에만 가능합니다. (탄약및 유류 재보급은 본부에서 재 활성화 시킬수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: エンジニアのトラックや修理トラックがエンジニアの近くにない場合、これは一度しか動作しません。（リロードと燃料補給能力はベースで元に戻すことができます）
Key.Original: That only works once if no engineer truck or repair truck is near an engineer (reload and refuel capability can be restored at base).
Key.Russian: Инженеры могут восстанавливать свою способность чинить возвращаясь на базу или к ремонтному грузовику.
Key.Chinesesimp: 只有工程车在附近才可以修理(补充弹药和油料需要在主基地进行).

Key.English: Engineers can also load static weapons like mortars, etc, into an engineer trucks and unload them wherever they want.
Key.Spanish: Los ingenieros también pueden cargar armas estáticas como morteros, etc, en sus camiones de reparaciones y descargarlas donde quiera.
Key.Portuguese: Os engenheiros também podem carregar armas estáticas como morteiros, etc, a uns caminhões de engenheiro e lhes descarregar wherever querem.
Key.Korean: 공병은 박격포와 같은 거치무기를 공병트럭에 적재하고, 어디서든 내릴 수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: エンジニアは、迫撃砲などの設置兵器をエンジニアのトラックに積み込み、必要な場所に降ろすことができます。
Key.Original: Engineers can also load static weapons like mortars, etc, into an engineer trucks and unload them wherever they want.
Key.Russian: Так же инженеры могут загружать статичное вооружение в свой специальный инженерный грузовик.
Key.Chinesesimp: 工程兵可以随时将固定武器，如迫击炮装载入卡车并卸载出来.

Key.English: Engineers are also able to flip vehicles that are lying upside down when they have a Toolkit (in the AI version every player can do that).
Key.Spanish: Los ingenieros también son capaces de voltear los vehículos que estén al revés cuando tiene un kit de herramientas (en la versión AI cada jugador puede hacer eso).
Key.Portuguese: Os engenheiros são também capazes a veículos de dedo que é lying ao revés quando têm um Toolkit (no AI versão a cada jogador pode fazer aquele).
Key.Korean: 공병은 도구모음을 가지고 있는 상태에서 뒤집어지거나 넘어진 차량을 뒤집을 수 있습니다. (AI전에서는 모든 유저 가능합니다.)
Key.Japanese: エンジニアは、ツールキットを持っているときに逆さまになっている車両を反転することもできます（AIのバージョンでは、すべてのプレーヤーがそれを行うことができます）。
Key.Original: Engineers are also able to flip vehicles that are lying upside down when they have a Toolkit (in the AI version every player can do that).
Key.Russian: Еще им доступна функция переворота техники (требуется ремнабор).
Key.Chinesesimp: 工程兵当他们有工具包Toolkit时还可以将翻车的车救治 (在AI模式中，任何人都可以).

Key.Japanese: %1 を両チームに
Key.Russian: Ящиков доступно одновременно на карте до %1 штук.

Key.English: The map at your base can be used as a teleporter to your mobile respawns or you can choose parajump there (if enabled).
Key.Spanish: El mapa de su base puede ser utilizado como un teletransportador a sus MHQs móviles o puede elegir saltar en paracaídas (si está activado).
Key.Portuguese: O mapa de sua Base pode ser utilizado como um teletransportador um seus MHQs móveis ou pode eleger saltar em paracaídas (se está ativado).
Key.Korean: 본부에 배치되여있는 지도로 지휘차량으로의 이동 혹은 공수낙하를 하실 수 있습니다. (활성화가 되어있을 시)
Key.Japanese: あなたの基地の地図はあなたのMHQへのテレポーターとして使うことができます。または、あなたがそこでパラジャンプを選択することもできます。（可能な場合）
Key.Original: The map at your base can be used as a teleporter to your mobile respawns or you can choose parajump there (if enabled).
Key.Russian: Вы можете телепортироваться с базы на КШМ и обратно или использовать затяжной прыжок с базы (если доступен).
Key.Chinesesimp: 主基地里的地图可以用来选择传送重生或者跳伞. (如果启用).

Key.English: If a vehicle that you've won for solving a sidemission or clearing a main target gets destroyed you can transport the wreck with chopper 4 (W) to the wreck repair point at your base and you'll get a new one after some time.
Key.Spanish: Si se destruye un vehículo que ha ganado por resolver una misión secundaria o eliminar un objetivo principal, se puede transportar la chatarra con el helicóptero 4 (W) hasta el punto de reparación de chatarra de su base y obtendrá uno nuevo después de algún tiempo.
Key.Portuguese: Se um veículo que tem ganhado para solucionar um sidemission ou aclarando um objetivo principal consegue destruído pode você transportar o wreck com chopper 4 (W) ao wreck ponto de reparo em vossa base e você conseguirão um novo um após que algum tempo.
Key.Korean: 만약 사용하던 장비가 작전 중 반파 되었을 경우, 4호 헬기 (W)를 통해 본부로 수송해온 뒤, 잔해 수리 지점에 배치하면 일정 시간뒤 동일 차량이 재 생성됩니다.
Key.Japanese: ミッションで手に入れた車両が破壊された場合、残骸を4番ヘリコプター(W)で修復ポイントに運ぶこび、しばらく待つことで新しい車両を手に入れることができます。
Key.Original: If a vehicle that you've won for solving a sidemission or clearing a main target gets destroyed you can transport the wreck with chopper 4 (W) to the wreck repair point at your base and you'll get a new one after some time.
Key.Russian: Если ПРИЗОВАЯ техника уничтожена по какой-то причине, Вы можете взять спецвертолет ('W' на карте -'врек') и отбуксировать эту технику на базу для восстановления.
Key.Chinesesimp: 当支线任务奖励的载具被摧毁后,你可以通过直升机Chopper 4 (W)吊运回残骸到修理点修理,需要一定的时间修理.

Key.English: Chopper 4 (W) can only transport wrecks, nothing else.
Key.Spanish: Helicóptero 4 (W) sólo se pueden transportar restos de chatarra, nada más.
Key.Portuguese: hopper 4 (W) só pode transportar wrecks, nada mais.
Key.Korean: 4호 헬기 (W)는 오직 장비 잔해만 나를 수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: 4番ヘリコプター(W)は残骸しか運べません
Key.Original: Chopper 4 (W) can only transport wrecks, nothing else.
Key.Russian: Только врек-вертолет (W) может перевозить обломки призовой техники.
Key.Chinesesimp: 直升机Chopper 4 (W) 只能运送残骸，不能作为其他用途.

Key.English: The artillery operators can execute artillery strikes (artillery targets have to be marked first, needs laser designator).
Key.Spanish: The artillery operators can execute artillery strikes (artillery targets have to be marked first, needs laser designator).
Key.Portuguese: The artillery operators can execute artillery strikes (artillery targets have to be marked first, needs laser designator).
Key.Korean: The artillery operators can execute artillery strikes (artillery targets have to be marked first, needs laser designator).
Key.Japanese: The artillery operators can execute artillery strikes (artillery targets have to be marked first, needs laser designator).
Key.Original: The artillery operators can execute artillery strikes (artillery targets have to be marked first, needs laser designator).
Key.Russian: Арт.наводчик вызывает арт.удар (Сначала отмечаете цель лазер. целецказателем, нужна батарейка к нему).
Key.Chinesesimp: 炮兵可以操作武器炮击 (首先要用激光指示仪标定炮击位置). 他们也可以拯救人质 (AI模式下所有人都可以). 炮兵需要将人质护送回地图上的基地.

Key.English: The leaders of team Alpha, Charlie and Echo can request air drops (in the AI version every player can do that, not available in the TT version). They can also mark artillery targets for the artillery operator (needs laser designator).
Key.Spanish: Los líderes de equipos Alpha, Charlie y Echo pueden solicitar suministros aéreos (en la versión AI cada jugador puede hacer eso, no disponible en la versión TT). También pueden marcar los objetivos de artillería para el operador de artillería (necesita un designador láser).
Key.Portuguese: Os dirigentes de Alfa de equipe, Charlie e Eco podem pedir gotas de ar (no AI versão a cada jogador pode fazer que, não disponível no TT versão). Podem também objetivos de artilharia da marca para o operador de artilharia (laser de necessidades designator).
Key.Korean: 알파, 찰리, 그리고 에코 분대장은 공수지원을 요청할 수 있습니다. (AI전에서는 모든 유저가 가능합니다. 팀전에서는 제공되지 않습니다). 또한 분대장들은 포격목표를 지시하여 포격지원을 받을수 있습니다. (레이저 지시기가 필요합니다.)
Key.Japanese: チームアルファ、チャーリー、エコーのリーダーは、空中投下を要求することができます（AIバージョンではすべてのプレイヤーができます、TTバージョンでは利用できません）。 彼らはまた、Artillery operatorのための砲撃目標をマークすることができます。（レーザー照準器が必要です）
Key.Original: The leaders of team Alpha, Charlie and Echo can request air drops (in the AI version every player can do that, not available in the TT version). They can also mark artillery targets for the artillery operator (needs laser designator).
Key.Russian: Командиры отделений Альфа, Чарли и Эхо могут вызывать авиаподдержку (в версии с наемом ИИ любой игрок может это делать). Так же они могут ТОЛЬКО отмечать цели для наводчика артиллерии (необходим лазерный целеуказатель)
Key.Chinesesimp: 队长可以进行跳伞 (AI模式下所有人都可以,TT模式仅队长).队长可以标记炮兵目标,需要激光指示仪.

Key.Spanish: Los médicos pueden colocar una tienda sanitaria.
Key.Korean: 의무병은 이동식 의무실(Mobile Army Sugical Hospital; MASH)를 설치할 수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: メディックはメディックテント(Mobile Army Sugical Hospital; MASH)を設置できます。
Key.Russian: Медики могут строить полевые медпункты, от лечения в которых они получают дополнительные очки.
Key.Chinesesimp: 医疗兵可以放置医疗帐篷.

Key.English: You can also change the viewdistance and other settings in the status dialog.
Key.Spanish: También puede cambiar la vista de distancia y otros ajustes en el menú de estado.
Key.Portuguese: Também pode mudar o viewdistance e outros enquadres no diálogo de estado.

Key.Japanese: また、ステータスダイアログで表示距離やその他の設定を変更することもできます。
Key.Original: You can also change the viewdistance and other settings in the status dialog.
Key.Russian: Вы можете изменить дальность обзора в меню через клавишу (U).
Key.Chinesesimp: 你可以在互动菜单中改变视距和其他设定.

Key.English: The revive system used in Dom is a little bit different to what you may be used to.
Key.Spanish: El sistema de revive utilizado en Dom es un poco diferente a lo que se puede utilizar.
Key.Portuguese: O reviver o sistema utilizado em Dom é um pouco diferente a que pode costumar.
Key.Korean: 여기서 사용되는 리바이브 시스템은, 기존의 리바이브 시스템과 미비하게 다릅니다.
Key.Japanese: Domで使用されている復活システムは、あなたが慣れ親しんだものと少し異なります。
Key.Original: The revive system used in Dom is a little bit different to what you may be used to.
Key.Russian: Вы можете ПЕРЕВОДИТЬ очки другим игрока своей стороны.
Key.Chinesesimp: DOMINATION中的救治系统可能跟你以前的习惯不太一样.

Key.English: Unconscious units play a death animation and not the usual roll around on the ground spasm animations.
Key.Spanish: Unidades inconscientes tiene una animación de moribundo y no el rollo de siempre con animaciones de espasmo en tierra.
Key.Portuguese: Unconscious As unidades jogam uma animação de morte e não o corro habitual ao redor na terra spasm animações.
Key.Korean: 상태불능인 캐릭터는 기존에 들어눕는 행동대신, 특유의 제스쳐를 합니다.
Key.Japanese: 意識不明のユニットは、死亡動作を再生し、けいれん動作中は通常のロールはできません。
Key.Original: Unconscious units play a death animation and not the usual roll around on the ground spasm animations.
Key.Russian: Для этого Вам нужно нажать U и следовать меню.
Key.Chinesesimp: 昏迷的玩家将有特定的动画,并不是通常在地上滚动抽搐的动画.

Key.English: You can drag unconscious units in prone position too.
Key.Spanish: Puede arrastrar unidades inconscientes en posición prono.
Key.Portuguese: Pode arrastar unconscious unidades em prone posição também.
Key.Korean: 누워서도 상태불능인 캐릭터를 끌고 올 수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: 意識のないユニットを伏せたまま運ぶこともできます。
Key.Original: You can drag unconscious units in prone position too.
Key.Russian: Все действия сохраняются в базе данных сервера.
Key.Chinesesimp: 你可以卧倒时拖动昏迷的玩家.

Key.English: Open the paramaters dialog in the server lobby to see a list of available features that you can change ingame before mission start (an admin must do that).
Key.Spanish: Abra los parámetros en el vestíbulo del servidor para ver una lista de funciones disponibles que puede cambiar dentro del juego antes de iniciar la misión (un administrador tiene que hacer eso).
Key.Portuguese: Aberto o paramaters diálogo no servidor lobby para ver uma lista de características disponíveis que pode você mudar ingame dantes de que início de missão (um admin tem que fazer aquele).
Key.Korean: 매개변수창(paramaters)를 열어 미션을 시작하기 전 세부설정을 확인하고 수정하실 수 있습니다. (관리자만 가능합니다)
Key.Japanese: サーバロビーのパラメータダイアログを開いて、ミッション開始前に変更可能な機能のリストを表示します。（管理者がそれを行う必要があります）
Key.Original: Open the paramaters dialog in the server lobby to see a list of available features that you can change ingame before mission start (an admin must do that).
Key.Russian: Все настройки миссии вы можете увидеть прямо в игре нажав карту и выбрав закладку -ЖУРНАЛ-.
Key.Chinesesimp: 在服务器大厅打开参数对话框能看到正在使用的功能参数列表，你可以在任务开始时修改游戏参数（必须登录管理员才能修改）.

Key.Korean: 매우 훌륭합니다. 메인 목표를 위한 Airdrop 코드가 유용할 것으로 보입니다.
Key.Japanese: 非常に素晴らしい。 メインターゲットのためのこれらのエア・ドロップ・コードが有用であると思われる。
Key.Original: Very nice. Seems these airdrop codes for main targets could prove useful.
Key.Russian: Отлично. Эти коды могут быть полезными для нас.
Key.Chinesesimp: 很好,看来获得敌军对主目标进行空投的代码很有用.

Key.English: Yeah. Finally able to know when those fighters show up. Now, if we only had something to fight them with.
Key.Spanish: Sí. Finalmente sabemos cuando los combatientes aparecen. Ahora, si sólo tuviéramos algo para luchar contra ellos.
Key.Portuguese: Yeah. Finalmente capaz de saber quando aqueles lutadores aparecem. Agora, se só tivemos algo para lhes lutar com.
Key.Korean: 좋습니다. 마침내 적군이 어디에 나타날 지 알 수있습니다. 이제, 울리는 그들가 싸울 물품이 필요합니다.
Key.Japanese: ついに、敵の戦闘機がいつ現れるかを知ることができる。もし私たちが彼らと戦うものがあれば。
Key.Original: Yeah. Finally able to know when those fighters show up. Now, if we only had something to fight them with.
Key.Russian: Да, теперь мы знаем, когда бойцы появяться. Было бы чем с ними бороться.
Key.Chinesesimp: 太棒了, 终于知道敌军什么时候出现了.现在,就看我们有什么武器能干他们了.

Key.English: Jolly bloody crap good. Finally some early warnings possible against those attack choppers.
Key.Spanish: Una puñetera mierda. Finalmente algunos posibles avisos contra los helicópteros de ataque.
Key.Portuguese: Jolly Sangrento caga bem. Finalmente alguns os avisos temporões possíveis contra aquele ataque choppers.
Key.Korean: 매우 아주 훌륭합니다. 마침내 공격 헬기에대한 조기경보가 가능해졌습니다.
Key.Japanese: 非常に、非常に素晴らしいです。最終的に攻撃ヘリコプターの早期警報が可能となりました。
Key.Original: Jolly bloody crap good. Finally some early warnings possible against those attack choppers.
Key.Russian: Jolly bloody crap good. Finally some early warnings possible against those attack choppers.
Key.Chinesesimp: 真是个好消息.终于对敌军攻击直升机有预警了.

Key.English: Code name for the MG chopper. Could be useful.
Key.Spanish: Código de nombre para el helicóptero MG. Podría ser útil.
Key.Portuguese: Nome de código para o MG chopper. Poderia ser útil..
Key.Korean: MG헬기의 코드네임. 매우 유용할 것 같습니다.
Key.Japanese: MGヘリコプターのコード名。 役に立つかもしれない。
Key.Original: Code name for the MG chopper. Could be useful.
Key.Russian: Кодовое имя для боевого вертолета. Может быть полезно.
Key.Chinesesimp: 获得敌军机枪武装的直升机的代号,会很有用.

Key.English: Niiiiice. They can shell us, but they can't hit us. Not anymore.
Key.Spanish: Biennnnn. Nos pueden pagar, pero no nos pueden atacar. Nunca más.
Key.Portuguese: Niiiiice. Podem-nos pelar, mas não nos podem colar. Não anymore.
Key.Korean: 아~주 좋습니다. 그들은 더이상 우리를 방어할 수 있지만, 공격할 수 없습니다.
Key.Japanese: Niiiiice。 彼らは私たちを殻にすることができますが、私たちを打つことはできません。 もう違います。
Key.Original: Niiiiice. They can shell us, but they can't hit us. Not anymore.
Key.Russian: Отлично. Они могут напасть на нас, но не уничтожить.
Key.Chinesesimp: 好消息!他们可以炮击我们,但再也打不中我们了.再也不能了.

Key.English: Don't they know they shouldn't put tracking devices on their patrol vehicles? Handy.
Key.Spanish: ¿No saben que no deben poner los dispositivos de localización en sus vehículos de patrulla? Manejable.
Key.Portuguese: Não sabem não teriam que pôr seguindo dispositivos em seus veículos patrulleros? Manejable.
Key.Korean: 그들은 순찰차량에 추적체를 붙이면 안된다는걸 모르는가? Handy.
Key.Japanese: 彼らは彼らのパトロール車両に追跡装置を置くべきではないことを知っていませんか？ ハンディ。
Key.Original: Don't they know they shouldn't put tracking devices on their patrol vehicles? Handy.
Key.Russian: Разве они не знают, что должны иметь gps-модули на машинах? Это удобно.
Key.Chinesesimp: 难道他们不知道不应该在他们的巡逻载具上装跟踪装置吗？非常方便哦！

Key.English: The information you found is already known.

Key.Original: The information you found is already known.
Key.Russian: Информация, которую вы обнаружили, уже известна.
Key.Chinesesimp: 你发现的信息已经知道了.

Key.English: This is a mobile respawn vehicle. You can load or drop an ammocrate, and if deployed you can use it to respawn, teleport, create a vehicle or satellite view.
Key.Spanish: Este es un vehículo respawn móvil. Puede cargar o descargar una caja de munición, si se ha implementado, se puede utilizar para reaparecer, teletransportarse, sacar un vehículo o vista por satélite.
Key.Portuguese: Isto é um móvel respawn veículo. Pode carregar ou cair um ammocrate, e se despregou-se pode-o utilizar a respawn, teleport, criar um veículo ou vista de satélite.
Key.Korean: 이것은 MHQ(지휘차량)입니다. 탄약상자를 적재하거나 하적할 수 있으며, 지휘차량을 전개(deploy)시, 해당 위치로 텔레포트, 재투입이 가능하며, 또한 차량 소환과 위성관측를 사용하실 수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: これは移動復活車です。 弾薬箱を搭載または投下することができます。展開されている場合は、復活、テレポート、車両の作成、衛星視点の利用ができます。
Key.Original: This is a mobile respawn vehicle. You can load or drop an ammocrate, and if deployed you can use it to respawn, teleport, create a vehicle or satellite view.
Key.Russian: Это мобильная точка возрождения (КШМ). Можете загрузить в нее ящик-арсенал, телепортироваться с\на базу, возрождаться на ней и смотреть через спутник за противником.
Key.Chinesesimp: 这是一个移动重生载具.你可以装载或卸载弹药箱,部署后你可以进行重生,传送,获得载具和卫星监控.

Key.English: This is an engineer truck. You can load static weapons and unload them.

Key.Original: This is an engineer truck. You can load static weapons and unload them.

Key.Original: The prototype was destroyed before it reached your base...
Key.Russian: Прототип был уничтожен и не доставлен на базу....
Key.Chinesesimp: 原型机已经在返回基地前被摧毁了...

Key.English: The pilots where killed before they reached the base...
Key.Spanish: Los pilotos murieron antes de llegar a la base...
Key.Portuguese: Os pilotos onde assassinados dantes de que conseguiram a base...
Key.Japanese: パイロットは基地に戻る前に死亡しました...
Key.Original: The pilots where killed before they reached the base...
Key.Russian: Пилоты были убиты до их спасения...
Key.Chinesesimp: 飞行员在返回基地前被杀死了...

Key.English: The enemies reached the cruise missile before us...
Key.Spanish: Los enemigos llegaron al misil de crucero antes que nosotros...
Key.Portuguese: Os inimigos conseguiram o míssil de cruzeiro dantes de que nos...
Key.Korean: 적이 크루즈 미사일에 아군보다 먼저 당도하였습니다.
Key.Japanese: 敵が我々よりも早く巡航ミサイルにたどり着きました...
Key.Original: The enemies reached the cruise missile before us...
Key.Russian: Противник нашел крылатую ракету раньше Вас...
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人在我们之前找到了巡航导弹...

Key.English: The flag was not delivered to base...
Key.Spanish: La bandera no se entregó en la base...
Key.Japanese: 旗は基地に届きませんでした...
Key.Original: The flag was not delivered to base...
Key.Russian: Флаг не был доставлен на базу...

Key.Japanese: サイドミッション未解決

Key.English: Good job. The tower is down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. La torre está abajo
Key.Portuguese: Bom trabalho. A torre está caída
Key.Japanese: タワーの破壊を確認。よくやった。
Key.Original: Good job. The tower is down.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好！塔台已经被摧毁！

Key.English: The enemy officer is dead. Good job.
Key.Spanish: El oficial enemigo está muerto. Buen trabajo.
Key.Portuguese: O agente de inimigo é morrido. Trabalho bom.
Key.Korean: 장교가 그 값을 물었습니다. 정의는 승리합니다. 수고하셨습니다.
Key.Japanese: 敵の将校の死亡を確認。よくやった
Key.Original: The enemy officer is dead. Good job.
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌军军官已经死亡，干得好！

Key.English: Good job. The artillery cannon is destroyed.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El cañón de artillería ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O canhão de artilharia está destruído.
Key.Japanese: 長距離砲は破壊された。よくやった。
Key.Original: Good job. The artillery cannon is destroyed.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得漂亮！远程火炮已经摧毁!

Key.English: There is a lighthouse on an island. Enemy ships use it to find their way to the around the coast, destroy it.
Key.Spanish: There is a lighthouse on an island. Enemy ships use it to find their way to the around the coast, destroy it.
Key.Portuguese: There is a lighthouse on an island. Enemy ships use it to find their way to the around the coast, destroy it.
Key.Korean: There is a lighthouse on an island. Enemy ships use it to find their way to the around the coast, destroy it.
Key.Japanese: There is a lighthouse on an island. Enemy ships use it to find their way to the around the coast, destroy it.
Key.Original: There is a lighthouse on an island. Enemy ships use it to find their way to the around the coast, destroy it.
Key.Russian: На острове есть маяк. Корабли противника используют его для навигации. Уничтожьте его!
Key.Chinesesimp: 岛上有一座灯塔. 敌军船只用于引导航行通往海岸.摧毁它！

Key.English: Good job. The lighthouse is destroyed.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El faro ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O faro está destruído.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。灯台は破壊された
Key.Original: Good job. The lighthouse is destroyed.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干的好!灯塔已经被摧毁.

Key.English: The enemy uses a radio tower to command its armored troops. Simple task, destroy it.
Key.Spanish: The enemy uses a radio tower to command its armored troops. Simple task, destroy it.
Key.Portuguese: The enemy uses a radio tower to command its armored troops. Simple task, destroy it.
Key.Korean: Lysina 산 정상에 라디오 타워가 있습니다. 적은 해당 기지를 통해 기갑병력을 통솔하고있다 합니다. 무력화하고 파괴시키십시오.
Key.Japanese: Lysina山の頂上にラジオタワーがある。敵はこれを装甲車両隊の指揮に利用してるようだ。それを破壊しろ。
Key.Original: The enemy uses a radio tower to command its armored troops. Simple task, destroy it.
Key.Russian: Противник использует радиовышку для вызова подкреплений. Задача проста - уничтожьте ее!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人用无线电塔台指挥他们的装甲部队.任务很简单,摧毁这个通讯站.

Key.English: Good job. The transformer station is down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. La estación transformadora ha sido destruída.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. A estação de transformador é abaixo.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。変電所は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The transformer station is down.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!变电站已经被摧毁.

Key.English: An enemy train is waiting in Elektrozavodsk for loading tanks and fuel. Find the train and destroy it!
Key.Spanish: Un tren enemigo está a la espera en Elektrozavodsk para la carga de tanques y combustible. ¡Encuentre el tren y destrúyalo!
Key.Portuguese: Um trem de inimigo está esperando em Elektrozavodsk para carregar tanques e combustível. Encontrar o trem e destruí-lo!
Key.Japanese: 敵の列車がElektrozavodskで戦車と燃料の積み込みを待っている。この列車を見つけ出して破壊しろ!
Key.Original: An enemy train is waiting in Elektrozavodsk for loading tanks and fuel. Find the train and destroy it!
Key.Russian: Железнодорожный состав проивника ожидает загнрузки танков и топлива к ним. Уничтожьте состав!
Key.Chinesesimp: 一列敌人的火车在Elektrozavodsk准备装载坦克和油料.找到并摧毁!

Key.English: Good job. The train is down...
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El tren ha sido destruído...
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. Ou trem é fazer
Key.Korean: Good job. The train is down...
Key.Japanese: よくやった。列車は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The train is down...
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!火车已经被摧毁...

Key.English: Good job. You got the prototype plane.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. Tiene el avión prototipo.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. Conseguia o avião de protótipo .
Key.Korean: Good job. You got the prototype plane.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。試作飛行機を手に入れた。
Key.Original: Good job. You got the prototype plane.
Key.Russian: Отличная работа! Вы захватили прототип авиации!
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得漂亮!你得到了测试的新型飞机.

Key.English: Good job. The convoy is down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El convoy ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O convoy é abaixo.
Key.Korean: Good job. The convoy is down.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。護送隊は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The convoy is down.

Key.English: The enemy uses a fuelstation to refuel its vehicles. Simple task, destroy it to cut down fuel supplies.
Key.Spanish: The enemy uses a fuelstation to refuel its vehicles. Simple task, destroy it to cut down fuel supplies.
Key.Portuguese: The enemy uses a fuelstation to refuel its vehicles. Simple task, destroy it to cut down fuel supplies.
Key.Korean: The enemy uses a fuelstation to refuel its vehicles. Simple task, destroy it to cut down fuel supplies.
Key.Japanese: The enemy uses a fuelstation to refuel its vehicles. Simple task, destroy it to cut down fuel supplies.
Key.Original: The enemy uses a fuelstation to refuel its vehicles. Simple task, destroy it to cut down fuel supplies.
Key.Russian: Противник использует заправочную станцию для дозаправки техники. Приказ - уничтожить ее!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人使用加油站站给车辆加油。任务很简单，摧毁它减少敌军燃料供应。

Key.English: Good job. The fuelstation is down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. La estación de combustible ha sido destruída.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O fuelstation é abaixo.
Key.Korean: Good job. The fuelstation is down.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。給油所は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The fuelstation is down.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!加油站已经完蛋了.

Key.English: Good job. The specops are eliminated.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. Los specops han sido eliminados.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O specops está eliminado.
Key.Korean: Good job. The specops are eliminated.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。特殊部隊は排除された。
Key.Original: Good job. The specops are eliminated.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得漂亮!特种部队已被歼灭.

Key.English: Good job. All tanks are down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. Todos los depósitos has sido destruídos.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. Todos os tanques são abaixo.
Key.Korean: Good job. All tanks are down.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。戦車はすべて破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. All tanks are down.

Key.English: Good job. You got the enhanced tank version.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. Tiene la versión mejorada del tanque.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. Conseguia a versão de tanque realçada .
Key.Korean: Good job. You got the enhanced tank version.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。改良型の戦車を手に入れた。
Key.Original: Good job. You got the enhanced tank version.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!你把坦克偷回来了.

Key.English: We want to provoke the enemy. Find the enemy flag and bring it back to the flag at your base.
Key.Spanish: We want to provoke the enemy. Find the enemy flag and bring it back to the flag at your base.
Key.Portuguese: We want to provoke the enemy. Find the enemy flag and bring it back to the flag at your base.
Key.Korean: We want to provoke the enemy. Find the enemy flag and bring it back to the flag at your base.
Key.Japanese: We want to provoke the enemy. Find the enemy flag and bring it back to the flag at your base.
Key.Original: We want to provoke the enemy. Find the enemy flag and bring it back to the flag at your base.
Key.Russian: Вам приказано сломить моральный дух противника. Найдите вражеский флаг и доставьте его к нам на базу!
Key.Chinesesimp: 我们要激怒敌人了.找到敌人的旗帜,偷走它并带回基地的旗帜处.

Key.English: Good job. The enemy flag is in our base.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. La bandera enemiga está en nuestra base.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. A bandeira de inimigo é em nossa base.
Key.Korean: Good job. The enemy flag is in our base.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。旗は無事に基地に届いた
Key.Original: Good job. The enemy flag is in our base.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!旗帜已经送回基地了.

Key.English: The enemy is building a prison. Destroy the building so that they can not arrest innocent people.
Key.Spanish: The enemy is building a prison. Destroy the building so that they can not arrest innocent people.
Key.Portuguese: The enemy is building a prison. Destroy the building so that they can not arrest innocent people.
Key.Korean: The enemy is building a prison. Destroy the building so that they can not arrest innocent people.
Key.Japanese: The enemy is building a prison. Destroy the building so that they can not arrest innocent people.
Key.Original: The enemy is building a prison. Destroy the building so that they can not arrest innocent people.
Key.Russian: Противник построил тюрьму. Уничтожьте здание, чтобы спасти гражданских от арестов!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人正在修建监狱.摧毁这个监狱，不要让他们监禁无辜的人.

Key.English: Good job. The prison is destroyed.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. La prisión ha sido destruída.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. A prisão está destruída.
Key.Korean: Good job. The prison is destroyed.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。刑務所は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The prison is destroyed.

Key.English: The enemy is producing biological weapons. Find the watertower that is needed for the production and destroy it.
Key.Spanish: The enemy is producing biological weapons. Find the watertower that is needed for the production and destroy it.
Key.Portuguese: The enemy is producing biological weapons. Find the watertower that is needed for the production and destroy it.
Key.Korean: The enemy is producing biological weapons. Find the watertower that is needed for the production and destroy it.
Key.Japanese: The enemy is producing biological weapons. Find the watertower that is needed for the production and destroy it.
Key.Original: The enemy is producing biological weapons. Find the watertower that is needed for the production and destroy it.
Key.Russian: Враг производит биологическое оружие. Найдите водонапорную башню, которая нужна для производства и уничтожьте ее!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌军在生产生化武器. 找到生产所用的水塔并摧毁.

Key.English: Good job. The water tower is down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El depósito de agua ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. A torre de água é abaixo.
Key.Korean: Good job. The water tower is down.
Key.Japanese: 給水塔は破壊された。よくやった。
Key.Original: Good job. The water tower is down.

Key.English: In the huge radio tower on top of mount Green Mountain is a IED, it looks like an ammobox. Your job is it to destroy the IED.
Key.Spanish: En la torre de radio de la parte superior del monte de Green Mountain hay un IED, se ve como una caja de munición. Su trabajo es destruir el IED.
Key.Portuguese: Na torre radiofónica enorme acima de montar a montanha Verde é um IED , parece um ammobox. Vosso trabalho é para destruir o IED.
Key.Korean: In the huge radio tower on top of mount Green Mountain is a IED, it looks like an ammobox. Your job is it to destroy the IED.
Key.Japanese: Green山の頂上にあるラジオタワーにIEDが仕掛けられた。それは大きな弾薬箱の形をしている。君の仕事はこれを破壊することだ。
Key.Original: In the huge radio tower on top of mount Green Mountain is a IED, it looks like an ammobox. Your job is it to destroy the IED.
Key.Russian: Радиовышка заминирована фугасом, который выглядит как брошенный ящик. Найдите и уничтожьте фугас!
Key.Chinesesimp: 在Green Mountain的巨型通讯站有一个IDE, 看起来象一个武器箱.你的任务是解除这个IDE.

Key.English: Good job. The IED got destroyed.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El IED fue destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O IED conseguiu destruído.
Key.Korean: Good job. The IED got destroyed.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。IEDは破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The IED got destroyed.

Key.English: The enemy is producing chemical weapons in a factory Solnichniy. Find the container that has some of the chemical for the production and destroy it.
Key.Spanish: El enemigo está produciendo armas químicas en una fábrica en Solnichniy. Busque el contenedor de productos químicos y destrúyalo.
Key.Portuguese: O inimigo está produzindo armas químicas em uma fábrica Solnichniy. Encontrar o contêiner que tem alguns da substância química para a produção e o destruir.
Key.Korean: The enemy is producing chemical weapons in a factory Solnichniy. Find the container that has some of the chemical for the production and destroy it.
Key.Japanese: Solnichniy工場で敵が化学兵器を製造している。製造な必要な薬品が積まれたコンテナを探して破壊しろ。
Key.Original: The enemy is producing chemical weapons in a factory Solnichniy. Find the container that has some of the chemical for the production and destroy it.
Key.Russian: Протинки производит хим.оружие на заводе возле Солнечного. Найдите контейнер и уничтожьте его!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人在Solnichniy附近的一个工厂生产化学武器. 找到一个化学武器的集装箱并摧毁.

Key.English: Good job. The cargo truck is destroyed.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El camión de carga ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O cargo o caminhão está destruído.
Key.Korean: Good job. The cargo truck is destroyed.
Key.Japanese: カーゴトラックは破壊された。よくやった。
Key.Original: Good job. The cargo truck is destroyed.

Key.English: Good job. The container is destroyed.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El contenedor de productos químicos ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O contêiner está destruído.
Key.Korean: Good job. The container is destroyed.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。コンテナは破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The container is destroyed.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!集装箱已被摧毁.

Key.English: Good job. The prisoners are free.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. Los prisioneros han sido liberados.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. Os prisioneiros são livres.
Key.Korean: Good job. The prisoners are free.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。囚人たちは解放された。
Key.Original: Good job. The prisoners are free.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!囚犯们被解救了.

Key.English: Good job. The officer was arrested.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El oficial ha sido detenido.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O agente esteve preso.
Key.Korean: Good job. The officer was arrested.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。将校は逮捕された。
Key.Original: Good job. The officer was arrested.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好！军官被抓回来了.

Key.English: Good job. You got the prototype chopper.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. Tiene el helicóptero prototipo.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. Conseguia o protótipo chopper
Key.Korean: Good job. You got the prototype chopper.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。新型ヘリコプターを手に入れた。
Key.Original: Good job. You got the prototype chopper.
Key.Russian: Отличная работа! Вы доставили прототип вертолета!
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好.你得到了原型直升机.

Key.English: The enemy has all its gold in a bank in Elektrozavodsk. Destroy the building so that they can't pay their weapon shipments anymore.
Key.Spanish: El enemigo tiene todo su oro en un banco de Elektrozavodsk. Destruya el edificio de modo que no pueden pagar sus envíos de armas.
Key.Portuguese: O inimigo tem todo seu ouro em um banco em Elektrozavodsk. Destruir o edifício de maneira que não podem pagar sua arma shipments anymore
Key.Korean: The enemy has all its gold in a bank in Elektrozavodsk. Destroy the building so that they can't pay their weapon shipments anymore.
Key.Japanese: 敵はElektrozavodskにある銀行にすべての金を預けている。 建物を破壊して、これ以上兵器の輸入をできないようにしろ。
Key.Original: The enemy has all its gold in a bank in Elektrozavodsk. Destroy the building so that they can't pay their weapon shipments anymore.
Key.Russian: Противник складирует свои золотые запасы в банке в Электрозаводске. Уничтожьте здание банка!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人的黄金存在Elektrozavodsk一家银行里. 摧毁那栋建筑别让他们再购买军火.

Key.English: Good job. The bank building is down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El edificio del banco ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O edifício de banco é abaixo.
Key.Korean: Good job. The bank building is down.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。銀行は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The bank building is down.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得漂亮.银行大楼已经摧毁.

Key.English: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory in Chernogorsk. Destroy the main building and the two chimneys to stop the production.
Key.Spanish: El enemigo tiene una fábrica de producción de bolas de rodamientos en Chernogorsk. Destruya el edificio principal y las dos chimeneas para detener la producción.
Key.Portuguese: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory in Chernogorsk. Destroy the main building and the two chimneys to stop the production.
Key.Korean: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory in Chernogorsk. Destroy the main building and the two chimneys to stop the production.
Key.Japanese: 敵はChernogorskの工場でボールベアリングを生産している。 主要建物と2つの煙突を破壊して生産を停止させろ。
Key.Original: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory in Chernogorsk. Destroy the main building and the two chimneys to stop the production.
Key.Russian: Протинки производит вооружение на заводе возле Черногорска. Найдите главное здание и две химлаборатории и уничтожьте их!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人在Chernogorsk的一家工厂生产轴承. 摧毁工厂的主楼和2个烟囱！

Key.English: Good job. The factory is down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. La fábrica ha sido destruída.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. A fábrica é abaixo.
Key.Korean: Good job. The factory is down.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。工場は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The factory is down.
Key.Russian: Отличная работа! Фабрика разрушена до основания!

Key.English: The enemy is producing ammunition in a factory near Berezino. Destroy the main building and the pipelines to stop the production.
Key.Spanish: El enemigo esta produciendo municiones en una fábrica cerca de Berezino. Destruir el edificio principal y los oleoductos para detener la producción.
Key.Portuguese: O inimigo está produzindo munição em uma fábrica próxima Berezino. Destruir o edifício principal e os encanamentos para parar a produção.
Key.Korean: The enemy is producing ammunition in a factory near Berezino. Destroy the main building and the pipelines to stop the production.
Key.Japanese: 敵はBerezino近くの工場で弾薬を生産している。 主要建物とパイプラインを破壊して生産を停止させろ。
Key.Original: The enemy is producing ammunition in a factory near Berezino. Destroy the main building and the pipelines to stop the production.
Key.Russian: Протинки производит вооружения на заводе возле Березино. Найдите главное здание и трубопровод и остановите производство!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人在Berezino附近生产弹药. 摧毁主楼和传输管道让他们停止生产！

Key.English: Intel reports about a train with vital military equipment leaving Chernogorsk habour soon. Find the train and destroy it!
Key.Spanish: El servicio de inteligencia informa acerca de un tren con un equipo vital militar que dejará pronto Chernogorsk. ¡Encuentre el tren y destrúyalo!
Key.Portuguese: Intel Relatórios sobre um trem com o equipamento militar vital que deixa Chernogorsk habour cedo. Encontrar o trem e destruí-lo!
Key.Korean: Intel reports about a train with vital military equipment leaving Chernogorsk habour soon. Find the train and destroy it!
Key.Japanese: 情報部がChernogorsk港をすぐに出発する重要な軍用機材を備えた電車について報告している。 電車を見つけてそれを破壊しろ！
Key.Original: Intel reports about a train with vital military equipment leaving Chernogorsk habour soon. Find the train and destroy it!
Key.Russian: Мы получили информацию со спутника о поезде с военным грузом у Черногорска. Найдите и взорвите его!
Key.Chinesesimp: 情报显示有一辆运有重要军事设备的火车即将离开Chernogorsk港口. 找到并摧毁这辆火车!

Key.English: Good job. All artillery guns are down. No artillery observers will appear at main targets anymore.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. Todas las piezas de artillería están destruídas. No aparecerán más observadores de artillería en los objetivos principales.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. Todas pistolas de artilharia são abaixo. Nenhum observadores de artilharia aparecerão em objetivos principais anymore.
Key.Korean: Good job. All artillery guns are down. No artillery observers will appear at main targets anymore.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。すべての敵長距離砲を破壊した。砲兵観測手がメインターゲットに現れることはもうないだろう。
Key.Original: Good job. All artillery guns are down. No artillery observers will appear at main targets anymore.
Key.Russian: Отличная работа. Все артнаводчики уничтожены, теперь противник не сможет на нас наводить минометы.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!所有的敌人大炮都被摧毁了,主要目标不会再出现敌人炮兵观察手了.

Key.English: Good job. The crew is back at base.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. La tripulación está de vuelta en la base.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. A tripulação está de volta em base.
Key.Korean: Good job. The crew is back at base.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。クルーは無事基地に戻った。
Key.Original: Good job. The crew is back at base.
Key.Russian: Отличная работа! Экипаж спасен и доставлен на базу!
Key.Chinesesimp: 干的好!机组人员已经成功返回基地.

Key.English: The enemy is building a hangar. Funny thing is, there is no airfield near that position. So, destroy that hangar before we really know what it is for.
Key.Spanish: The enemy is building a hangar. Funny thing is, there is no airfield near that position. So, destroy that hangar before we really know what it is for.
Key.Portuguese: The enemy is building a hangar. Funny thing is, there is no airfield near that position. So, destroy that hangar before we really know what it is for.
Key.Korean: The enemy is building a hangar. Funny thing is, there is no airfield near that position. So, destroy that hangar before we really know what it is for.
Key.Japanese: The enemy is building a hangar. Funny thing is, there is no airfield near that position. So, destroy that hangar before we really know what it is for.
Key.Original: The enemy is building a hangar. Funny thing is, there is no airfield near that position. So, destroy that hangar before we really know what it is for.
Key.Russian: Противник построил ангар для будующих испытаний техники. Приказ - уничтожить его полностью!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人在建立了一个机库. 有趣的是,附近没有机场.所以在我们弄清楚这机库到底是干什么用的之前摧毁机库!

Key.English: Good job. The hangar is down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El hangar ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O hangar é abaixo.
Key.Korean: Good job. The hangar is down.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。格納庫は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The hangar is down.
Key.Russian: Отличная работа! От ангара остались руины!
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得漂亮!机库已经被摧毁.

Key.English: There is an enemy training facility. Destroy the main building to cut down their possibilities to train new soldiers.
Key.Spanish: There is an enemy training facility. Destroy the main building to cut down their possibilities to train new soldiers.
Key.Portuguese: There is an enemy training facility. Destroy the main building to cut down their possibilities to train new soldiers.
Key.Korean: There is an enemy training facility. Destroy the main building to cut down their possibilities to train new soldiers.
Key.Japanese: There is an enemy training facility. Destroy the main building to cut down their possibilities to train new soldiers.
Key.Original: There is an enemy training facility. Destroy the main building to cut down their possibilities to train new soldiers.
Key.Russian: Обнаружен тренировочный лагерь боевиков! Уничтожьте основное здание чтобы разрушить инфраструктуру лагеря!
Key.Chinesesimp: 有一个敌军训练营. 摧毁主楼减少敌人的新兵培训能力.

Key.English: Good job. The main building of the training facility is destroyed.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El edificio principal de las instalaciones de entrenamiento ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: bom Trabalho. O edifício principal da facilidade de formação está destruído
Key.Korean: Good job. The main building of the training facility is destroyed.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。敵訓練施設は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The main building of the training facility is destroyed.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!训练基地的主要设施已经被摧毁.

Key.English: Good job. The helicopter is destroyed.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El helicóptero ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O helicóptero está destruído.
Key.Korean: Good job. The helicopter is destroyed.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。ヘリコプターは破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The helicopter is destroyed.
Key.Russian: Отличная работа! Вертолет больше не взлетит!

Key.English: Good job. The plane is destroyed.
Key.Spanish: Good job. The plane is destroyed.
Key.Portuguese: Good job. The plane is destroyed.
Key.Korean: Good job. The plane is destroyed.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。飛行機は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The plane is destroyed.
Key.Russian: Отличная работа! Самолет больше не взлетит!

Key.English: A terrorist leader called Nib Nedal hides somewhere. Your task is to find him and eliminate him!
Key.Spanish: A terrorist leader called Nib Nedal hides somewhere. Your task is to find him and eliminate him!
Key.Portuguese: A terrorist leader called Nib Nedal hides somewhere. Your task is to find him and eliminate him!
Key.Korean: A terrorist leader called Nib Nedal hides somewhere. Your task is to find him and eliminate him!
Key.Japanese: A terrorist leader called Nib Nedal hides somewhere. Your task is to find him and eliminate him!
Key.Original: A terrorist leader called Nib Nedal hides somewhere. Your task is to find him and eliminate him!
Key.Russian: Обнаружен лидер террористической организации острова. Срочно найдите и ликвидируйте его!
Key.Chinesesimp: 一个恐怖份子的头目叫Nib Nedal隐藏在北部山区某处. 你的任务是找到他并消灭他！

Key.English: The terrorist leader is dead. Good job.
Key.Spanish: El líder terrorista ha muerto. Buen trabajo.
Key.Portuguese: O dirigente terrorista é morrido. Trabalho bom.
Key.Korean: The terrorist leader is dead. Good job.
Key.Japanese: テロリストリーダーの死亡を確認。よくやった
Key.Original: The terrorist leader is dead. Good job.
Key.Chinesesimp: 恐怖分子头目已经消灭!干得好!

Key.English: The enemy is producing chemical weapons. Find the cargo truck that has some of the chemicals for the production and destroy it.
Key.Spanish: The enemy is producing chemical weapons. Find the cargo truck that has some of the chemicals for the production and destroy it.
Key.Portuguese: The enemy is producing chemical weapons. Find the cargo truck that has some of the chemicals for the production and destroy it.
Key.Korean: The enemy is producing chemical weapons. Find the cargo truck that has some of the chemicals for the production and destroy it.
Key.Japanese: The enemy is producing chemical weapons. Find the cargo truck that has some of the chemicals for the production and destroy it.
Key.Original: The enemy is producing chemical weapons. Find the cargo truck that has some of the chemicals for the production and destroy it.
Key.Russian: Противник производит химическое оружие. Найдите и уничтожьте грузовик противника с хим.оружием!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人在营地里生产化学武器. 找到装有化学武器的卡车并摧毁掉.

Key.English: An enemy officer is on a walk in a forrest nearby. This is a good chance to arrest him and bring him to your base.
Key.Spanish: An enemy officer is on a walk in a forrest nearby. This is a good chance to arrest him and bring him to your base.
Key.Portuguese: An enemy officer is on a walk in a forrest nearby. This is a good chance to arrest him and bring him to your base.
Key.Korean: An enemy officer is on a walk in a forrest nearby. This is a good chance to arrest him and bring him to your base.
Key.Japanese: 敵の将校が近くの森で散歩中だ。 彼を逮捕し、基地に連行するいいチャンスだ。
Key.Original: An enemy officer is on a walk in a forrest nearby. This is a good chance to arrest him and bring him to your base.
Key.Russian: Один из высших чинов протинока прогуливается по лесу. Ликвидируйте его!
Key.Chinesesimp: 一个敌人军官在附近散步. 这是一个很好的机会把他抓回来审讯.

Key.English: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory. Destroy the fuel tanks to stop the production.
Key.Spanish: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory. Destroy the fuel tanks to stop the production.
Key.Portuguese: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory. Destroy the fuel tanks to stop the production.
Key.Korean: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory. Destroy the fuel tanks to stop the production.
Key.Japanese: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory. Destroy the fuel tanks to stop the production.
Key.Original: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory. Destroy the fuel tanks to stop the production.
Key.Russian: Противник хранит запасы нефти для производства топлива для танков. Приказ штаба -уничтожить хранилище!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人有一个轴承工厂.摧毁油料罐,停止他们的生产!

Key.English: Good job. The fuel tanks are down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. Los tanques de combustible han sido destruídos.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. Os tanques de combustível são abaixo.
Key.Korean: Trabalho bom. Os tanques de combustível são abaixo.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。燃料タンクは破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The fuel tanks are down.
Key.Russian: Отличная работа! Только прибавили забот гринписовцам!
Key.Chinesesimp: 很好!油料罐都被摧毁了.

Key.English: The enemy has some very productive oil pumps near Nagara-1-Oilfield. Destroy the pumps there to cut down the enemy fuel supllies.
Key.Spanish: El enemigo tiene algunas bombas de petróleo muy productiva cerca de Nagara-1-Oilfield. Destruya las bombas para reducir el combustible.
Key.Portuguese: O inimigo tem algum azeite muito produtivo bombea próximo Nagara-1-Oilfield. Destruir as bombas ali para cortar abaixo o combustível de inimigo supllies.
Key.Korean: The enemy has some very productive oil pumps near Nagara-1-Oilfield. Destroy the pumps there to cut down the enemy fuel supllies.
Key.Japanese: 敵はNagara-1-油田の近くに非常に優良なオイルポンプをいくつか持っています。 敵の燃料供給を減らすためにそこにあるポンプを破壊しろ。
Key.Original: The enemy has some very productive oil pumps near Nagara-1-Oilfield. Destroy the pumps there to cut down the enemy fuel supllies.
Key.Russian: Противник захватил нефтяные насосы около Нагары. Уничтожьте их чтобы ослабить обеспечение протинкиа!
Key.Chinesesimp: 在Nagara-1-油田附近有一些油泵. 摧毁这些油泵切断他们的油料补给.

Key.English: Good job. The oil pumps are down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. Las bombas de petróleo están destruídas.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. As bombas de azeite são abaixo.
Key.Korean: Good job. The oil pumps are down.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。 オイルポンプは停止した。
Key.Original: Good job. The oil pumps are down.
Key.Russian: Отличная работа. Все нефтяные насосы уничтожены!
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!油泵已经被摧毁.

Key.English: The enemy is testing a new helicopter prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.
Key.Spanish: The enemy is testing a new helicopter prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.
Key.Portuguese: The enemy is testing a new helicopter prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.
Key.Korean: The enemy is testing a new helicopter prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.
Key.Japanese: The enemy is testing a new helicopter prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.
Key.Original: The enemy is testing a new helicopter prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.
Key.Russian: Противник тестирует прототип самолета. Уничтожьте его до испытаний!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人有新型直升机在进行测试。在敌军使用之前摧毁它。

Key.English: The enemy tests a new plane prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.
Key.Spanish: The enemy tests a new plane prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.
Key.Portuguese: The enemy tests a new plane prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.
Key.Korean: The enemy tests a new plane prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.

Key.Original: The enemy tests a new plane prototype. Destroy it before enemy troops use it.

Key.Chinesesimp: 敌军有新型直升机在进行测试. 摧毁它!

Key.Chinesesimp: 发现在 %1 的敌方弹药车并摧毁.

Key.Russian: Найдите радар ВВС в %1 и взорвите его!
Key.Chinesesimp: 在 %1 找到对空雷达并摧毁

Key.English: Find a collaborateur in %1 and eliminate him

Key.Chinesesimp: 在 %1 找到敌军同盟者并消灭

Key.English: Find a drug dealer who sells drugs to our troops in %1 and eliminate him
Key.Spanish: Encuentre un traficante de drogas que vende drogas a nuestras tropas en %1 y elimínelo.
Key.Portuguese: Encontrar um comerciante de fármaco quem vende fármacos a nossas tropas em %1 e lhe eliminar
Key.Korean: %1에 아군에게 마약을 판매한 마약상을 찾아 제거하십시오.

Key.Chinesesimp: 在%1找到向我们军队兜售毒品的毒贩,消灭他!

Key.Spanish: Hay una fábrica de barcos enemigos cerca de Iremi Bay. Destruya el edificio para reducir sus posibilidades de construir nuevos barcos.
Key.Portuguese: Há uma fábrica de barca do inimigo próximo Iremi Bahia. Destruir o edifício para cortar abaixo suas possibilidades para construir Barcas novas.
Key.Korean: There is an enemy boat factory near Iremi Bay. Destroy the building to cut down their possibilities to build new Boats.
Key.Japanese: Iremi湾の近くに敵の造船所がある。これを破壊して新たな船が作られる可能性を減らせ。
Key.Original: There is an enemy boat factory near Iremi Bay. Destroy the building to cut down their possibilities to build new Boats.
Key.Russian: Обнаружен завод по производству лодок. Уничтожьте его!
Key.Chinesesimp: 在Iremi海湾附近有一个造船厂摧毁建筑不要让他们再生产船只了.

Key.English: Good job. The boat factory is destroyed.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. La fábrica de barcos ha sido destruída.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. A fábrica de barca está destruída.
Key.Korean: Good job. The boat factory is destroyed.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。造船所は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The boat factory is destroyed.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!船厂已经被摧毁.

Key.English: The sniper is down. Good job.
Key.Spanish: El francotirador ha sido eliminado. Buen trabajo.
Key.Portuguese: O francotirador é abaixo. Trabalho bom.
Key.Japanese: スナイパーは排除された。よくやった
Key.Original: The sniper is down. Good job.
Key.Chinesesimp: 狙击手被干掉了,好样的!

Key.English: Find and Capture the sniper in a forest near Molos, he is wanted for killing innocent civilians. Don't spook him as he will run. Beware there are enemy patrols in the area.
Key.Spanish: Busque y Capture a un francotirador en el bosque cerca de Molos, es buscado por el asesinato de civiles inocentes. Cuidado hay patrullas enemigas en la zona.
Key.Portuguese: Encontra e Capturar o francotirador no bosque próximo Molos, está querido para matar civis inocentes. Não spook lhe tão corra. Beware Há patrulhas de inimigo no área.
Key.Korean: Molos 숲속에 숨어있는 저격수를 생포하십시오. 그는 무고한 시민을 사살하여 수배중입니다. 추가적인 정찰 병력이 있을 수 있으니 주의하십시오.
Key.Japanese: Molosの近くの森の中のスナイパーを見つけて捕まえろ。彼は罪のない市民を射殺して手配中だ。この地域では敵のパトロールが行われている、注意しろ。
Key.Original: Find and Capture the sniper in the forest near Molos, he is wanted for killing innocent civilians. Don't spook him as he will run. Beware there are enemy patrols in the area.
Key.Russian: Найдите и захватите в плен снайпера в лесах рядом с Молосом.Не дайте ему сбежать! Помните о патрулях противника в районе поиска!
Key.Chinesesimp: 在 Molos 附近丛林去找到并抓捕一个狙击手, 他想射杀无辜的村民. 别放过他,他会逃跑,附近也有敌军巡逻队.

Key.English: Well Done, now we can put him on trial for his crimes
Key.Spanish: Bien hecho, ahora podemos llevarlo a juicio por sus crímenes
Key.Portuguese: Bem Fato, agora lhe podemos pôr em cima prova para seus delitos
Key.Korean: 수고하셨습니다. 그는 곧 심판을 통해 죗값을 치루게 될것입니다.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。彼は裁判で罪が問われるだろう
Key.Original: Well Done, now we can put him on trial for his crimes
Key.Russian: Хорошо, теперь мы можем подвергнуть его суду за его преступления
Key.Chinesesimp: 很好,现在我们可以审判他了!

Key.English: Good job. You got the APC.
Key.Spanish: Good job. You got the APC.
Key.Portuguese: Good job. You got the APC.
Key.Korean: Good job. You got the APC.
Key.Japanese: Good job. You got the APC.
Key.Original: Good job. You got the APC.

Key.English: Your rank %1 does not allow you to take a %2. Aborted! Check your magazines!
Key.Spanish: Su rango %1 no permite coger un %2. ¡Abortado! Compruebe sus cargadores.
Key.Portuguese: Vossa faixa %1 não deixa você para tomar um %2. Abortado! Controle vossas revistas!
Key.Korean: Your rank %1 does not allow you to take a %2. Aborted! Check your magazines!
Key.Japanese: %1には%2を手にすることは許可されていません。中止します。マガジンを確認してください!
Key.Original: Your rank %1 does not allow you to take a %2. Aborted! Check your magazines!
Key.Russian: Ваше звание %1 не позволяет Вам взять %2. Проверьте какие магазины у Вас остались!
Key.Chinesesimp: 你的级别是 %1 不允许拾取 %2. 动作已取消,请检查你的弹夹!

Key.Spanish: Sólo los jugadores pueden reclutar AI.
Key.Portuguese: Os jogadores únicos podem recrute AI!
Key.Korean: 오직 플레이어만 AI를 모집할 수 있습니다.
Key.Japanese: プレーヤーだけAIを募集することができます。

Key.English: There are some special operations boats in a bay near Pacamac that enemy SF forces use for secret missions. Find them and destroy them.
Key.Spanish: Hay algunos barcos de operaciones especiales en una bahía cerca de Pacamac, las fuerzas SF enemigas los usan para misiones secretas. Encontrarlos y destruirlos.
Key.Portuguese: Há alguns barcas de operações especiais em uma baía próxima Pacamac que inimigo SF força uso para missões secretas. Encontra-lhes e destruir-lhes.
Key.Korean: There are some special operations boats in a bay near Pacamac that enemy SF forces use for secret missions. Find them and destroy them.
Key.Japanese: 特殊部隊の使っているボートがPacamac近くにある。敵特殊部隊が秘密任務に使っているようだ。探して破壊しろ。
Key.Original: There are some special operations boats in a bay near Pacamac that enemy SF forces use for secret missions. Find them and destroy them.
Key.Russian: Обнаружен причал с лодками для спец операций рядом с г.Пакамак. Противник использует их для проведения секретных миссий. Найдите и уничтожьте лодки!
Key.Chinesesimp: 在Pacamac发现执行秘密任务的敌军特种兵船只,找到船只并摧毁.

Key.English: Good job. The boats are down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. Los barcos han sido destruídos.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. As barcas são abaixo.
Key.Korean: Good job. The boats are down.
Key.Japanese: ボートは破壊された。よくやった。
Key.Original: Good job. The boats are down.

Key.English: An enemy scientist is experimenting with volcano technology on Monte Asharah. We don't know yet what it's all about but it is better that he doesn't progress. Eliminate him!
Key.Spanish: Un científico enemigo está experimentando con la tecnología de volcán en Monte Asharah. No sabemos todavía de qué se trata todo esto, pero es mejor que no progresa. Elimínelo.
Key.Portuguese: Um cientista de inimigo é experimenting com tecnologia de vulcão em Monte Asharah. Não sabemos ainda que é tudo aproximadamente mas é melhor que não progride. Elimina-lhe!
Key.Korean: An enemy scientist is experimenting with volcano technology on Monte Asharah. We don't know yet what it's all about but it is better that he doesn't progress. Eliminate him!
Key.Japanese: 敵の科学者がMonte Asharahで火山技術の実験をしている。内容のすべてはまだわからないがやめさせるべきだと判断された。彼を排除しろ!
Key.Original: An enemy scientist is experimenting with volcano technology on Monte Asharah. We don't know yet what it's all about but it is better that he doesn't progress. Eliminate him!
Key.Russian: Некий ученый проводит испытания технологий связанных с извержением вулканов у горы Монте Ашарах. Мы не хотим, чтобы технилогии развивались далее. Ликвидируйте ученого!
Key.Chinesesimp: 一个敌方科学家在Monte Asharah进行火山实验.我们并不清楚试验的细节,干脆干掉他!

Key.English: The enemy scientist is dead. Good job.
Key.Spanish: El científico enemigo está muerto. Buen trabajo.
Key.Portuguese: O cientista de inimigo é morrido. Bom job.ps.
Key.Korean: The enemy scientist is dead. Good job.
Key.Japanese: 科学者の死亡を確認。よくやった。
Key.Original: The enemy scientist is dead. Good job.
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌方科学家被干掉了,漂亮!

Key.English: The enemy has all its gold in a bank in Bagango. Destroy the building so that they can't pay their weapon shipments anymore.
Key.Spanish: El enemigo tiene todo su oro en un banco en Bagango. Destruya el edificio de modo que no puedan pagar más sus envíos de armas.
Key.Portuguese: O inimigo tem todo seu ouro em um banco em Bagango. Destruir o edifício de maneira que não podem pagar sua arma shipments anymore.
Key.Korean: The enemy has all its gold in a bank in Bagango. Destroy the building so that they can't pay their weapon shipments anymore.
Key.Japanese: 敵はBagangoにある銀行にすべての金を預けている。 建物を破壊して、これ以上兵器の輸入をできないようにしろ。
Key.Original: The enemy has all its gold in a bank in Bagango. Destroy the building so that they can't pay their weapon shipments anymore.
Key.Russian: Противник хранит свои золотые запасы в банке в г. Баганго. Уничтожьте здание, чтобы враг не смог больше покупать оружие.
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人所有的黄金都在Bagango银行里.摧毁建筑物,让他们无法再购买军火.

Key.English: Good job. The bank building is down.
Key.Spanish: Buen trabajo. El edificio del banco ha sido destruído.
Key.Portuguese: Trabalho bom. O edifício de banco é abaixo.
Key.Korean: Good job. The bank building is down.
Key.Japanese: よくやった。銀行は破壊された。
Key.Original: Good job. The bank building is down.
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好!银行的楼已经被摧毁!

Key.English: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory near Paraiso. Destroy the two main buildings to stop the production.
Key.Spanish: El enemigo está produciendo bolas de rodamientos en una fábrica cerca de Paraiso. Destruya los dos edificios principales para detener la producción.
Key.Portuguese: O inimigo está produzindo pelota bearings em uma fábrica próxima Paraiso. Destruir os dois edifícios principais para parar a produção
Key.Korean: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory near Paraiso. Destroy the two main buildings to stop the production.
Key.Japanese: 敵はParaiso付近の工場でボールベアリングを生産している。 2つの主要建物を破壊して生産を停止させろ。
Key.Original: The enemy is producing ball bearings in a factory near Paraiso. Destroy the two main buildings to stop the production.
Key.Russian: Обнаружена завод противника по производству военного снаряжения. Ваша задача уничтожить два главных здания!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人在Paraiso附近的工厂生产轴承.摧毁2个主建筑物,停掉他们的生产.

Key.English: The enemy is producing ammunition in a factory near Somato. Destroy the hall and the chimney to stop the production.
Key.Spanish: El enemigo está produciendo municiones en una fábrica cerca de Somato. Destruya la sala y la chimenea para detener la producción.
Key.Portuguese: O inimigo está produzindo munição em uma fábrica próxima Somato. Destruir a sala e a lareira para parar a produção.
Key.Korean: The enemy is producing ammunition in a factory near Somato. Destroy the hall and the chimney to stop the production.
Key.Japanese: 敵はSomato付近の工場で弾薬を生産している。 ホールと煙突を破壊して生産を停止させろ。
Key.Original: The enemy is producing ammunition in a factory near Somato. Destroy the hall and the chimney to stop the production.
Key.Russian: Обнаружена фабрика противника по производству военного снаряжения. Ваша задача уничтожить ее!
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人在Somato附近的工厂生产弹药,摧毁厂房和烟囱!

Key.English: The king of Sedia is on vacation in a hotel near Vallejo. He is a good friend of the enemy leaders. Eliminate him!
Key.Spanish: El rey de Sedia está de vacaciones en un hotel cerca de Vallejo. Él es un buen amigo de los líderes enemigos. Elimínelo.
Key.Portuguese: O rei de Sedia é em cima férias em um hotel próximo Vallejo. É um amigo bom dos dirigentes de inimigo. Elimina-lhe!
Key.Korean: The king of Sedia is on vacation in a hotel near Vallejo. He is a good friend of the enemy leaders. Eliminate him!
Key.Japanese: Sediaの王がVallejo付近のホテルで休暇中だ。彼は敵軍リーダーの親しい友人のようだ。彼を排除しろ!
Key.Original: The king of Sedia is on vacation in a hotel near Vallejo. He is a good friend of the enemy leaders. Eliminate him!
Key.Russian: Король Седии отдыхает в отеле недалеко. Он хороший друг наших врагов. Ликвидируйте его!
Key.Chinesesimp: Sedia的国王在Vallejo附近度假. 他是敌军领导人的好朋友. 消灭他!

Key.English: The king of Sedia is dead. Good job.
Key.Spanish: El rey de Sedia ha muerto. Buen trabajo.
Key.Portuguese: O rei de Sedia é morrido. Trabalho bom.
Key.Korean: The king of Sedia is dead. Good job.
Key.Japanese: Sediaの王は死んだ。よくやった。
Key.Original: The king of Sedia is dead. Good job.

Key.Japanese: Base Flag

Key.English: Attention!!! You are using a NVG scope which is not allowed.\n\nRemoving it now, please choose another scope!
Key.Spanish: ¡¡¡Atención!!! Está utilizando un alcance NVG que no está permitido. \ En \ Extracción ahora, por favor elija otro alcance!
Key.Portuguese: Atenção!!! Está utilizando um NVG atinja que não é dejado.nnRemoving Ele agora, comprazer escolher outro alcance!
Key.Korean: Attention!!! You are using a NVG scope which is not allowed.\n\nRemoving it now, please choose another scope!
Key.Japanese: 注意!!!ナイトビジョンスコープは許可されていません。\n\nスコープを削除しました。ほかのスコープを使ってください!!
Key.Original: Attention!!! You are using a NVG scope which is not allowed.\n\nRemoving it now, please choose another scope!
Key.Russian: Внимание! Вы используете ПНВ прицел, который не разрешен\n\nОн удален, выберите другой прицел!
Key.Chinesesimp: 注意!!! 你所选择的夜视功能望远镜禁止使用.\n\n现在已经移除,请选择其他望远镜!

Key.English: Attention!!! You are using a TI scope which is not allowed.\n\nRemoving it now, please choose another scope!
Key.Spanish: ¡¡¡Atención!!! Está utilizando un ámbito de TI que no está permitido. \ En \ Extracción ahora, por favor elija otro alcance!
Key.Portuguese: Atenção!!! Está utilizando um TI atinja que não é dejado.nnRemoving Ele agora, comprazer escolher outro alcance!
Key.Korean: Attention!!! You are using a TI scope which is not allowed.\n\nRemoving it now, please choose another scope!
Key.Japanese: 注意!!!サーマルイメージスコープは許可されていません。\n\nスコープを削除しました。ほかのスコープを使ってください!!
Key.Original: Attention!!! You are using a TI scope which is not allowed.\n\nRemoving it now, please choose another scope!
Key.Russian: Внимание! Вы используете ТВП прицел, который не разрешен\n\nОн удален, выберите другой прицел!
Key.Chinesesimp: 注意!!! 你所选择的 TI 望远镜禁止使用.\n\n现在已经移除,请选择其他望远镜!

Key.Japanese: %1 投下
ターゲット無し

Key.English: Our forces are in urgent need of supplies. Deliver the supply truck from our Base to the point of destination
Key.Spanish: Nuestras fuerzas están en necesidad urgente de suministros. Entregar el camión de abastecimiento de nuestra base hasta el punto de destino
Key.Portuguese: Nossas forças são em necessidade urgente de fornecimentos. Entregar o caminhão de fornecimento de nossa Base no ponto de destino
Key.Korean: Our forces are in urgent need of supplies. Deliver the supply truck from our Base to the point of destination
Key.Japanese: 友軍が補給を必要としている。基地から補給地点まで補給トラックを届けなくてはならない
Key.Original: Our forces are in urgent need of supplies. Deliver the supply truck from our Base to the point of destination
Key.Russian: Наши подразделения нуждаются в пополнении запасов и БК. Ваша задача доставить грузовик со всем необходимым до места назначения
Key.Chinesesimp: 我们的军队急需补给.从基地护送补给卡车到目的地。

Key.English: Well done! The friendly forces have got the supplies
Key.Spanish: ¡Bien hecho! Las fuerzas amigas han conseguido los suministros
Key.Portuguese: Bem feito! As forças amistosas têm os fornecimentos
Key.Korean: Well done! The friendly forces have got the supplies
Key.Japanese: よくやった！ 友軍は補給を受け取った
Key.Original: Well done! The friendly forces have got the supplies
Key.Russian: Отлично. Наши войска получили снаряжение и БК!
Key.Chinesesimp: 干得好！友军已经得到了补给！

Key.English: The enemy has laid naval mines in the entrance to the bay. We need them disarmed to allow us access to the facility nearby.
Key.Spanish: El enemigo ha sembrado minas navales en la entrada de la bahía. Necesitamos desarmados para permitir el acceso a la instalación cercana.
Key.Portuguese: O inimigo tem posto minas navais na entrada à baía. Precisamos-lhes desarmados para deixar-nos acesso à facilidade próxima.
Key.Korean: The enemy has laid naval mines in the entrance to the bay. We need them disarmed to allow us access to the facility nearby.
Key.Japanese: 敵は湾の入り口に機雷を敷設した。 近くの施設にアクセスできるようにするには、機雷を除去しなければならない。
Key.Original: The enemy has laid naval mines in the entrance to the bay. We need them disarmed to allow us access to the facility nearby.
Key.Russian: Противник заминировал все подступы. Ваша задача срочно разминировать территорию.
Key.Chinesesimp: 敌人在入海湾的海口埋放了水雷.我们需要清除水雷确保水路通畅.

Key.English: The enemy has laid mines on a cross road. We need them disarmed to allow us access to the facility nearby.
Key.Spanish: El enemigo ha sembrado minas en una carretera transversal. Necesitamos desarmados para permitir el acceso a la instalación cercana.
Key.Portuguese: O inimigo tem pôs minas em uma estrada de cruz. Precisamos-lhes desarmados para deixar-nos acesso à facilidade próxima.
Key.Korean: The enemy has laid mines on a cross road. We need them disarmed to allow us access to the facility nearby.
